Bug 2
Problem:
The code uses hard-coded waits (time.sleep) instead of proper synchronizatio this can lead to flaky and slow tests
Fix:
Replace time.sleep with Playwright’s built-in waiting mechanisms

page.wait_for_selector("#search")
page.wait_for_selector(".result-item")

Bug 3
Problem:
The selector .button is too generic and may match multiple elements or break if the UI changes.
Fix:
Use a more stable and specific selector (e.g., ID or data-test attribute).

page.locator("[data-test='search-button']").click()
